# PATCH 010: Kimi K2.6 (kimi-for-coding) support
#
# Adds first-class support for the Kimi K2.6 coding model (upstream id
# "kimi-for-coding") to the fork. Mirrors the current kimi-cli / kosong SDK
# wire format so the backend routes our requests to the K2.6 generation
# instead of silently falling back to K2.5.
#
# Changes (scoped entirely to Kimi; no other providers touched):
#   - internal/runtime/executor/kimi_executor.go
#       * Advertise KimiCodeCLI/1.35.0 user-agent and X-Msh-Version=1.35.0
#       * New X-Msh-Os-Version header (GOOS + GOARCH)
#       * Whitelist "kimi-for-coding" in stripKimiPrefix so the literal
#         model id is forwarded verbatim to the backend
#       * New applyKimiPromptCacheKey() that attaches a deterministic
#         prompt_cache_key derived from sha256(authID || system || first
#         user message) ONLY for kimi-for-coding, matching kimi-cli's
#         llm.py behaviour. Client-provided prompt_cache_key wins.
#   - internal/auth/kimi/kimi.go
#       * Device-flow / refresh commonHeaders() now send
#         X-Msh-Platform=kimi_cli and X-Msh-Version=1.35.0 instead of the
#         old cli-proxy-api/1.0.0 identifier
#   - internal/thinking/provider/kimi/apply.go (+ test)
#       * When reasoning_effort is set, also set thinking.type="enabled"
#         (kosong wire format). Without this, K2.6 runs with thinking
#         silently disabled.
#   - internal/registry/model_definitions.go
#       * Static kimi-for-coding entry (262144 ctx, thinking-capable) so
#         the model stays registered even if the remote models.json catalog
#         is refreshed without it.
#
# All changes are gated to the Kimi provider / kimi-for-coding model id, so
# Antigravity, Copilot, Claude, Gemini, Codex, etc. behaviour is unchanged.
#
diff --git a/internal/auth/kimi/kimi.go b/internal/auth/kimi/kimi.go
index ccb1a6c2..5faf3f19 100644
--- a/internal/auth/kimi/kimi.go
+++ b/internal/auth/kimi/kimi.go
@@ -162,11 +162,19 @@ func getHostname() string {
